content: Idaho authorities have identified the two firefighters killed and a third firefighter badly wounded in Sunday's ambush in Coeur d'Alene

Zohran Mamdani, the favorite to become New York City's next mayor after winning the Democratic primary, has a contentious plan to create a network of city-owned grocery stores. But it's less radical than critics portray, some food policy and grocery industry experts say.

Two people have been killed in the Coeur d'Alene, Idaho, attack. Police remain under fire by high-powered rifles.

Republican Sen. Thom Tillis won't seek reelection. The news comes a day after the North Carolina lawmaker voted against Trump's domestic policy bill.

Iran's nuclear ambitions "obliterated" after US strikes, Defense Secretary Hegseth says. "Operation Midnight Hammer" involved more than 125 aircraft, and B-2 bombers were deployed over the Pacific as a "decoy," according to US officials. Follow live updates.

Follow live updates.

Update: Minnesota lawmaker and husband killed in "politically motivated assassination" by suspect posing as police, officials say. Another lawmaker was injured, and a manhunt is underway. Follow live updates.
